### Database Roles

Each database will have three database roles for layered access control:

| Role | Purpose | Inherits From |
|------|---------|---------------|
| `DB_R` | Read access to all objects | — |
| `DB_W` | Write access (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) | DB_R |
| `DB_C` | Create access (DDL operations) | DB_W |

These roles are connected to schema-level roles (created in the next step) and account functional roles.

